                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 351.117/55.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Sharp</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-11-09T16:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 9, 1915, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1089. Doctor Kirghis, bearer Departmental passport 8125, September 24, 1915,
                    naturalized citizen of the United States, French extraction, having left France
                    at age of thirteen years and returning last month to France from United States
                    to visit dying father, has been summoned for military service French army. Has
                    applied to me for protection. He is resident and property owner in Saint Cloud,
                    Minnesota, doctor by profession, and forty years of age. Am authorized to make
                    representations to Foreign Office?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sharp</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
